# Model Fine-Tuning – Customizing Pre-Trained LLMs for Specific Use Cases Mastery Checklist

Mastering Model Fine-Tuning means learning how to adapt a pre-trained Large Language Model (LLM) into a specialized model for a specific domain, company, workflow, or task.

Most AI applications start with:

```text
Prompt
 ↓
General Model
 ↓
Response
```

Fine-tuning introduces:

```text
Prompt
 ↓
Custom Model
 ↓
Specialized Response
```

Instead of repeatedly teaching behavior through prompts, fine-tuning permanently modifies model behavior through training.

Fine-tuning is one of the most misunderstood areas in AI engineering.

Many problems that beginners attempt to solve with fine-tuning should actually be solved with:

```text
Prompt Engineering

RAG

Tool Calling

Memory

Agents
```

A senior engineer must know when NOT to fine-tune.

