# Phase 0 — Why Fine-Tuning Exists

## Historical Context

Evolution of NLP systems:

```text
Task-Specific Models
 ↓
Transfer Learning
 ↓
Foundation Models
 ↓
Fine-Tuned Foundation Models
```

Early machine learning required:

```text
One Model
Per Task
```

Examples:

```text
Spam Detector

Sentiment Model

Translator

NER Model
```

Modern AI:

```text
One Foundation Model

Many Fine-Tuned Variants
```

---

## Problem It Solves

Base models are:

```text
General Purpose

Broad Knowledge

Generic Behavior
```

Organizations need:

```text
Company Knowledge

Domain Expertise

Custom Style

Specialized Skills
```

---

## Fine-Tuning Solution

Teach the model:

```text
Your Domain

Your Terminology

Your Tasks

Your Workflow
```

---

## Alternatives

### Prompt Engineering

Pros:

```text
Fast
Cheap
No Training
```

Cons:

```text
Limited Behavior Change
```

---

### RAG

Pros:

```text
Dynamic Knowledge

Fresh Data
```

Cons:

```text
External Infrastructure Required
```

---

### Fine-Tuning

Pros:

```text
Permanent Skill Adaptation
```

Cons:

```text
Training Cost
Maintenance
```

---

## Tradeoffs

| Problem   | Best Solution      |
| --------- | ------------------ |
| Knowledge | RAG                |
| Behavior  | Prompt Engineering |
| Skill     | Fine-Tuning        |
| Actions   | Agents             |

